The "fade in" command, fi, is used to smoothly increase the amplitude
at the start of the audio.  Type fi, a space, and the number of
seconds over which fading should be done.  The default is 1.0 seconds.
Fading is linear when the fading time is more than two seconds, and it
is S-shaped, or an ogive, when less.  This command may be undone with
the undo command, u.

